<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="137" pageId="15" pageNumber="136" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="136">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="136">Japan. K. Ito s.n. (lectotype, designated here: L! [L0170980]).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="137">
<pageBreakToken pageId="16" pageNumber="137" start="start">In</pageBreakToken>
the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation author="Blume, CL" journalOrPublisher="Museum Botanicum Lugduno-Batavum" pageId="19" pageNumber="140" pagination="1 - 25" refId="B1" refString="Blume, CL, 1849. Melastomataceae. Museum Botanicum Lugduno-Batavum 1: 1 - 25" title="Melastomataceae." volume="1" year="1849">Blume (1849)</bibRefCitation>
cited no specimen but the name &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhexia fasikan" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fasikan">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">Rhexia fasikan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (should be 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhexia hasikan" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hasikan">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">Rhexia hasikan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see below) attached to a specimen from Von 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Siebold’s">Siebold's</normalizedToken>
herbarium. Ohba and Akiyama (pers. comm.) discovered one sheet with the name &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhexia hasikan" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hasikan">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">Rhexia hasikan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; in the herbarium in Leiden (L0170980). The sheet contains two collections, a smaller one covered by paper on the upper part and a larger one with four branches on the middle and lower part. According to Ohba (pers. comm.), the epithet &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="hasikan" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hasikan">hasikan</taxonomicName>
&quot; comes from the Japanese name of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. hirsuta" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">B. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, viz. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Hashikan-boku”">&quot;Hashikan-boku&quot;</normalizedToken>
. This sheet is regarded as the type material of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. hirsuta" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">B. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We here designate the larger collection on the sheet as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. hirsuta" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">B. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
